sentences: Marta Savić (Serbian Cyrillic: Марта Савић; born 7 May 1966) is a Bosnian-born Serbian turbo-folk singer.
At the age of two months, her family settled in the Serbian town Jaša Tomić.
In 1978, the family relocated to Hannover, Germany, where she finished primary and secondary school.
In 1988 she met singer Mile Kitić, whom she later married.
In January 2013, Marta Savić underwent gallbladder surgery.
